---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Manifesto — Axiom Atelier">
  <section class="manifesto">
    <h1>On Essential Subtraction</h1>

    <p>
      I don't design furniture by adding decoration until it looks finished. I start with more
      material than the piece will ever need, and I take away everything that isn't essential —
      until what's left is inevitable. Not decorated. Not styled. Just true to what the wood
      already wanted to be.
    </p>

    <p>
      This is Latent Form Theory: the belief that the ideal form of a piece already exists
      inside the material. My job isn't to invent it. It's to find it, and remove everything
      standing in its way.
    </p>

    <p>
      Every piece that leaves this workshop is made entirely by my own hands — no delegation, no
      production line, no shortcuts. That's not a marketing claim. It's the only way I know how
      to make something honest.
    </p>

     <p>
      To learn more about my design philosophy, and the principles which guide my work, 
      <a href="https://latentformtheory.com">Visit the Latent Form Theory website.</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .manifesto {
    padding: 80px 0;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
    color: #2a2a2a;
  }
</style>